<table border="0" cellpadding="5" width="550" cellspacing="5" height="400" >
<tr valign="top" height="400" >
<td tEditID="c1r1" style=" background-color:#FFFFFF; bEditID:r3st1; color:#000000; bLabel:main; font-size:12pt; font-family:arial;" aEditID="c1r1" locked="0" >
<![CDATA[<div style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><div style=""><div style=""><div style=""><div style=""><font style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Hi {!Contact.FirstName},<br></font><br style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Thanks for getting in touch with Kingsbridge.</span><br style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><br style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">We are writing to confirm that, as per your request,</span><b style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">&nbsp;we have cancelled your insurance policy&nbsp;<i>(insert policy number)</i></b><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">&nbsp;with Kingsbridge&nbsp;</span><b style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">from the date of inception&nbsp;<i>(DD MMM YYYY)</i></b><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">.&nbsp;</span><br style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><br style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><u style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">It’s important to note that you are now no longer able to claim under this policy, so please disregard any previous documentation you have received from us as null and void</u><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">.</span><br style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><br style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Since your Kingsbridge insurance policy has been cancelled,&nbsp;</span><u style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">we want to ensure you're aware that your business may not be covered against claims if you don't have another insurance policy in place</u><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">. To help you stay protected, we recommend exploring alternative cover options. If you have any questions or need assistance, please don't hesitate to reach out to our customer service team.</span><br style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><br style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><br style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><b style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Cancelling your payment</b><br style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><br style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">As you paid for your policy in a single payment, a refund of&nbsp;</span><i style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">£XXX</i><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">&nbsp;will appear in the account from which you originally paid within 3 to 10 working days.</span><br style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><br style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><br style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><b style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Making a claim&nbsp;</b><br style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><br style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Although your previous insurance policy&nbsp;</span><i style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">(active between DD MMM YYYY to DD MMM YYYY)&nbsp;</i><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">with Kingsbridge expired, you may still be able to make a claim on this policy.&nbsp;</span><br style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><br style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Any claims submitted for the Professional Indemnity and Directors’ and Officers’ elements of the policy will not be met as these operate on a ‘claims made’ basis and therefore the policy must be live in order to respond.&nbsp;</span><br style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><br style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Any claims for the Personal Accident, Public Liability and Employers’ Liability elements for the time your policy was active can still be notified to insurers.&nbsp; Please refer to your&nbsp;</span><a href="https://www.kingsbridge.co.uk/policy-documents/" style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">policy wording</a><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">&nbsp;for full information.</span><br style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><br style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><i style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">(Use if for IR35 Add On)&nbsp;</i><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">IR35 Protect operates on a ‘claims made’ basis, so the policy must be active to respond to most claims. However, for&nbsp;</span><a href="https://www.kingsbridge.co.uk/policy-documents/" style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">sections 10-12</a><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">&nbsp;on your policy there is a 4-year extended reporting period for you to notify us of a claim for an investigation during the period your policy was active. Any claim in these sections must be notified to insurers within 30 days of an insured event taking place and before any response to HMRC. Your appointed representation will work with you to respond and manage communications with HMRC.&nbsp;</span><br style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><br style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><i style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">(Use for Legal Expenses)&nbsp;</i><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Legal Expenses cover operates on a ‘claims made’ basis and therefore the policy must be live in order to respond in the majority of claims. However, for&nbsp;</span><a href="https://www.kingsbridge.co.uk/policy-documents/" style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">section 10</a><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">&nbsp;on your policy there is a 4-year extended reporting period for you to notify us of a claim for an investigation during the period your policy was active. Any claim in these sections must be notified to insurers within 30 days of an insured event taking place and before any response to HMRC. Your appointed representation will work with you to respond and manage communications with HMRC.&nbsp;</span><br style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><br style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><i style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">(Use for Cyber Liability)&nbsp;</i><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Cyber Liability cover operates on a ‘claims made’ basis and therefore the policy must be live in order to respond in the majority of claims. For some sections of the cover however, you can notify us of a claim up to 30 days following your policy expiry date. Please see your&nbsp;</span><a href="https://www.kingsbridge.co.uk/policy-documents/" style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">policy wording</a><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">&nbsp;for full details.</span><br style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><br style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">If you are unsure whether you can make a claim on a cancelled policy, please contact our customer service team and we will be happy to help.&nbsp;</span><br style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><br style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><br style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><b style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Important information regarding your Professional Indemnity cover</b><br style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><br style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">As mentioned above,&nbsp;</span><u style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">you are now no longer able to claim on the Professional Indemnity part of your policy – we want to take the opportunity to make you aware that this may put your business at risk from claims</u><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">. However, there are still ways you can proactively manage this risk for continued peace of mind.&nbsp;</span><br style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><br style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">One such way to keep your business protected is a product called&nbsp;</span><b style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Run-Off Cover</b><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">&nbsp;that helps you to avoid any gap in cover. I’ve attached information on Kingsbridge’s Run-Off Cover for your interest, and you can simply reply to this email if you would like to learn more or to proceed with purchasing a Run-Off policy.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><br style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><br style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><br style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Whether you’re currently insured with Kingsbridge or not, our customer service team is always here to help. Please don’t hesitate to reply to this email if you need any further information on any of the above.</span><br style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><font style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><br>Kind regards,<br></font><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><br>{!User.FirstName}<br></span><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Customer Service Team<br></span><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><br>E:&nbsp;</span><a href="mailto:customersupport@kingsbridge.co.uk" style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">customersupport@kingsbridge.co.uk</a><br style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">T: 01242 808 740</span></div></div></div></div></div>]]></td>
</tr>
</table>